ode_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM0Mzg0NjMz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/34384633?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro", "html_url": "https://github.com/tdelabro", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2021-05-02T17:03:37Z", "updated_at": "2021-05-02T20:53:44Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When a doc comment refers to `Self` inside an `impl` block for a type that is not in scope, `rustdoc` can't properly resolve `Self`.\r\n\r\nIt does resolve `Self` to a more specific name (`Foo` in the example below), but then it can't find that name.\r\n\r\nA minimum example:\r\n```rust\r\nstruct Foo {\r\n\tfoo: i32,\r\n}\r\n\r\nmod bar {\r\n\timpl crate::Foo {\r\n\t\t/// Baz the [`Self::foo`].\r\n\t\tpub fn baz(&self) {\r\n\t\t\tprintln!(\"bazzing the foo\");\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis produces a broken link in the documentation and the following warning:\r\n```\r\n$ cargo doc\r\n Documenting foo v0.1.0 (/tmp/2021-05-02-18-45-24/foo)\r\nwarning: unresolved link to `Foo::foo`\r\n --> src/main.rs:7:16\r\n  |\r\n7 |         /// Baz the [`Self::foo`].\r\n  |                      ^^^^^^^^^^^ no item named `Foo` in scope\r\n  |\r\n  = note: `#[warn(rustdoc::broken_intra_doc_links)]` on by default\r\n\r\nwarning: 1 warning emitted\r\n\r\n    Finished dev [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.66s\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n\r\nI tested this using:\r\n\r\n* rustdoc 1.53.0-nightly (42816d61e 2021-04-24)\r\n* rustdoc 1.51.0 (2fd73fabe 2021-03-23)\r\n\r\nBoth show the same problem.\r\n\r\n@rustbot modify labels: +A-rustdoc\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"tdelabro\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/84827/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/84827/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}